SwiftUI Image view takes too much space if it's loading or having error. I want to have dynamic size for image. So it will be as big as loaded picture or as big as fits with aspectRatio fit. For loading and error I set max height. But view itself is still bigger and on screenshots can see white empty space.

Environment:
Kingfisher 8.10.0
Xcode  26.5 (17F42)
Swift 6.2
SwiftUI
iOS 26

Code:
```Swift
import Kingfisher
import SwiftUI

struct LazyImageWithKingFisher: View {
	let imageUrl: String

	var body: some View {
		KFImage(URL(string: imageUrl))
			.resizable()
			.placeholder {
				Color.gray
					.frame(maxHeight: 200)
					.border(.blue)
			}
			.onFailureView {
				Color.red
					.frame(maxHeight: 200)
					.border(.blue)
			}
			.clipShape(
				RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 12)
			)
			.aspectRatio(contentMode: .fit)
			.border(.red)
	}
}

#Preview {
	VStack(spacing: 0) {
		LazyImageWithKingFisher(
			imageUrl: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506744038136-46273834b3fb"
		)
		LazyImageWithKingFisher(
			imageUrl: "https://httpbin.org/delay/10"
		)
		Spacer()
	}
}
```
