```
When I convert the image I got from KingfisherManager using ` let data = media.image.jpegData(compressionQuality: 1.0) ` , its size is much larger than the original image. I can’t send this data to the backend because of a size limit. I need to get the original file size. Is there any way to get the original image data?

Ever since we updated to 8.6.0 a few months ago we started getting CONTINUATION MISUSE crashes in code that calls `KingfisherManager.shared.retrieveImage(with:options:)`

Here is an example of some of the code exhibiting the crash.

   ```
 func getImage(url: URL) async -> Image? {
        return await withCheckedContinuation { continuation in
            KingfisherManager.shared.retrieveImage(with: url) { result in
                switch result {
                case .success(let data):
                    let image = Image(uiImage: data.image)
                    continuation.resume(returning: image)
                case .failure:
                    continuation.resume(returning: nil)
                }
            }
        }
    }
```

